# Platform-Specific Guidelines

## Web Responsive

Reference: `.mba-template/platforms/web-responsive.md`

### Key Points
- Mobile-first approach
- Breakpoints: 640px, 768px, 1024px, 1280px
- Touch targets: 44px × 44px minimum
- Responsive typography
- Flexible layouts

## Desktop Apps (Electron/Tauri)

Reference: `.mba-template/platforms/desktop-apps.md`

### Window Management
- Title bar: 32-40px (Windows), 22px (macOS)
- Window controls: native or custom
- Drag region for moving window
- Resize from all edges

### Keyboard Shortcuts
- Cmd/Ctrl + N: New
- Cmd/Ctrl + S: Save
- Cmd/Ctrl + W: Close
- Cmd/Ctrl + Q: Quit
- Cmd/Ctrl + ,: Preferences

### Layout
- Menu bar: 28-32px
- Toolbar: 40-48px
- Sidebar: 240-280px (collapsible)
- Status bar: 24-28px

### Interaction
- Click targets: 24px × 24px minimum
- Hover states essential
- Right-click context menus
- Keyboard navigation

## iOS Mobile

Reference: `.mba-template/platforms/ios-mobile.md`

### Safe Areas
- Top: Status bar + notch (44-59pt)
- Bottom: Home indicator (34pt)
- Always respect safe area insets

### Navigation
- Navigation bar: 44pt (compact), 96pt (large title)
- Tab bar: 49pt, 2-5 tabs
- Back button: Automatic
- Swipe back gesture

### Typography
- SF Pro font family
- Dynamic Type support (12 sizes)
- Never use fixed sizes

### Colors
- System colors (adapt to light/dark)
- Semantic colors (label, background, etc.)
- Test in both modes

### Components
- Buttons: Filled, Gray, Tinted, Plain
- Lists: Inset, Grouped, Plain
- Sheets: Medium/Large detents
- Alerts: 1-2 buttons

### Touch Targets
- Minimum: 44pt × 44pt
- Recommended: 48pt × 48pt

### Gestures
- Tap, Long press, Swipe, Pinch, Drag
- Don't block system gestures

## Android Mobile

Reference: `.mba-template/platforms/android-mobile.md`

### Material Design 3
- Dynamic color from wallpaper
- Tonal palettes (13 tones)
- Elevation via tinting
- State layers for interaction

### Navigation
- Top app bar: 64dp
- Bottom navigation: 80dp, 3-5 items
- Navigation drawer: 360dp (standard)
- Navigation rail: 80dp (vertical)

### Typography
- Roboto font family
- Type scale: Display, Headline, Title, Body, Label
- Support system font scaling

### Colors
- Color roles (primary, secondary, tertiary, error)
- Surface tinting for elevation
- Light and dark themes

### Components
- Buttons: Filled, Filled Tonal, Outlined, Text, Elevated
- FAB: Small (40dp), Medium (56dp), Large (96dp)
- Cards: Elevated, Filled, Outlined
- Text fields: Filled, Outlined

### Touch Targets
- Minimum: 48dp × 48dp
- Spacing: 8dp between targets

### Gestures
- Tap, Long press, Swipe, Pinch
- System gesture navigation

## Cross-Platform Considerations

### Shared Principles
- Consistent spacing scale
- Semantic color system
- Clear visual hierarchy
- Accessible design
- Responsive layouts

### Platform Differences
- **Navigation**: iOS (bottom tabs), Android (bottom nav), Desktop (sidebar)
- **Typography**: SF Pro (iOS), Roboto (Android), System (Desktop)
- **Interactions**: Touch (mobile), Mouse+Keyboard (desktop)
- **Patterns**: Follow platform conventions

### Adaptive Design
```javascript
// Detect platform
const isIOS = /iPad|iPhone|iPod/.test(navigator.userAgent);
const isAndroid = /Android/.test(navigator.userAgent);
const isDesktop = !isIOS && !isAndroid;

// Apply platform-specific styles
if (isIOS) {
  // iOS-specific code
} else if (isAndroid) {
  // Android-specific code
} else {
  // Desktop code
}
```

## Platform-Specific Rules

### When Targeting iOS
- Use SF Pro font
- Respect safe areas
- Support Dynamic Type
- Use iOS components
- Follow Apple HIG
- Test with VoiceOver

### When Targeting Android
- Use Roboto font
- Implement Material Design 3
- Support dynamic color
- Use Material components
- Follow Material guidelines
- Test with TalkBack

### When Targeting Desktop
- Support keyboard shortcuts
- Implement window management
- Use native menus
- Support system theme
- Test keyboard navigation
- Respect system preferences

## Best Practices

### Do
- Follow platform conventions
- Use platform components
- Respect system preferences
- Test on target platforms
- Support platform gestures
- Use platform fonts
- Adapt to screen sizes

### Don't
- Force one design everywhere
- Ignore platform patterns
- Block system gestures
- Use wrong components
- Ignore accessibility
- Hardcode dimensions
- Skip platform testing
